rld War II | year = 2005 | origyear = 1994 | publisher = Cambridge University Press | location = Cambridge; Oxford | isbn = 978-0-521-85316-3 | ref = harv}}\n* {{cite book| last = Welch | first = David | title = Hitler: Profile of a Dictator | year = 2001 | publisher = Routledge | location = London | isbn = 978-0-415-25075-7 | ref = harv}}\n* {{cite web | last = Wiederschein | first = Harald | url = https://www.focus.de/wissen/mensch/geschichte/zweiter-weltkrieg/militaerisch-unbedeutend-brutal-verbrecherisch-mythos-waffen-ss-hitlers-ueberschaetzte-elitetruppen_id_4826676.html | title = Mythos Waffen-SS | work = [[Focus (German magazine)|Focus]] | date = 21 July 2015 | access-date = 3 October 2018 | language = German | ref = harv}}\n* {{cite web | last = Wrobel | first = Peter | work = The Devil's Playground: Poland in World War II | title = Warsaw Uprising 1944 | year = 1999 | publisher = The Canadian Foundation for Polish Studies of the Polish Institute of Arts & Sciences Price-Patterson Ltd | url = http://www.warsawuprising.com/paper/wrobel1.htm | ref = harv}}\n{{refend}}\n\n== External links ==\n{{Sister project links|Germany|commons=Category:National Socialism}}\n* {{Wikiatlas|Germany}}\n* {{cite web | title = Introduction to the Holocaust | publisher = [[United States Holocaust Memorial Museum]] | url = https://encyclopedia.ushmm.org/content/en/article/introduction-to-the-holocaust | encyclopedia = Holocaust Encyclopedia}}\n* [http://research.calvin.edu/german-propaganda-archive/ww2era.htm#Speech German Propaganda Archive] hosted by [[Calvin College]] {{in lang|en}}\n\n{{Navboxes\n|list =\n{{NSDAP}}\n{{Nazism}}\n{{States of Nazi Germany}}\n{{Germany topics}}\n{{Fascism}}\n{{Empires}}\n{{World War II}}\n{{Adolf Hitler}}\n}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n[[Category:1930s in Germany|.]]\n[[Category:1933 establishments in Germany|*]]\n[[Category:1940s in Germany|.]]\n[[Category:1945 disestablishments in Germany|*]]\n[[Category:20th century in Germany by period]]\n[[Category:Articles containing video clips]]\n[[Category:Axis powers]]\n[[Category:Fascist states|Germany]]\n[[Category:Modern history of Germany]]\n[[Category:Natalism]]\n[[Category:Nazi Germany| ]]\n[[Category:Nazism]]\n[[Category:States and territories disestablished in 1945]]\n[[Category:States and territories established in 1933]]\n[[Category:Totalitarian states]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=February 2019}}\n{{Redirect|Drittes Reich|the 1923 book|Das Dritte Reich}}\n{{pp-semi-indef}}\n{{pp-move-indef}}\n{{Short description|Germany from 1933 to 1945, while under control of the Nazi Party}}\n{{Coord|52|31|N|13|24|E|type:country_source:kolossus-ptwiki|display=title}}\n{{Good article}}\n{{EngvarB|date=October 2018}}\n{{Infobox former country\n|conventional_long_name = German Reich {{small|{{nobold|(1933\u20131943)}}<br />''Deutsches Reich''}}<hr />Greater German Reich {{small|{{nobold|(1943\u20131945)}}<br />''Gro\u00dfdeutsches Reich''}}<!-- do not replace with 'Nazi Germany', that's the modern COMMONNAME, whereas this parameter is for the official name -->\n|common_name            = Germany\n|era                    = [[Interwar period|Interwar]] / [[World War II]]\n|status                 = \n|status_text            = \n|government_type        = [[Nazism|Nazi]], [[One-party state|one-party]], [[Totalitarianism|totalitarian]] [[dictatorship]]\n<!-- rise and fall, events, years and dates -->\n|event_start            = [[Machtergreifung|Seizure of Power]]\n|date_start             = 30 January\n|year_start             = 1933\n|event_end              = [[Flensburg Government#Dissolution|Final dissolution]]\n|date_end               = 23 May\n|year_end               = 1945\n|event1                 = [[Enabling Act of 1933|Enabling Act]]\n|date_event1            = 23 March 1933\n|event2                 = [[Anschluss]]\n|date_event2            = 12 March 1938\n|event3                 = [[World War II]]\n|date_event3            = 1 September 1939\n|event4             